h in 1802 and again in 1807. The visits came during Burr's national political prominence and his subsequent flight from Eastern political circles after the Hamilton duel."},{"number":4,"category":"death","header":"Buried under maiden name Edwards to honor parents","body":"She died 1 September 1859 at Savannah Georgia and was buried at Laurel Grove Cemetery under the surname 'EDWARDS' — her birth name — chosen at death to honor her parents' memory. Her father Jonathan Edwards Jr and mother Mary Porter had both died when she was a young girl."}],"slug":"maria-edwards-1778"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}